00:45.311 --> 00:47.211
A Weekend Cinema
and Hong Film production

00:47.280 --> 00:49.544
Lotte Entertainment presents

01:14.607 --> 01:17.804
And like that,
Eva walks stone-faced,

01:17.877 --> 01:21.813
down the unfamiliar
streets of New York.

01:24.084 --> 01:29.522
With the black-and-white landscape
of the city behind her shoulder

01:29.589 --> 01:31.614
An unforgettable opening scene.

01:33.293 --> 01:34.885
From "Stranger than Paradise"

01:37.497 --> 01:41.831
In a few days, I'll be walking
those streets myself.

01:44.704 --> 01:48.697
Tomorrow will be my last show
before I leave for New York.

01:50.076 --> 01:53.739
I'm sad to leave but tomorrow.

01:53.813 --> 01:56.839
I'll wait for you here
at Midnight F.M.

01:57.917 --> 02:02.320
With the soundtrack
from "Stranger than Paradise"

02:02.388 --> 02:06.882
"l put a spell on you,"
I'll conclude tonight's broadcast

02:08.761 --> 02:12.595
Oh, and for the tickets to
"the Breaking News" premiere.

02:12.665 --> 02:15.896
keep your calls coming in,
all you thriller-lovers!

02:17.437 --> 02:23.000
Talking about the movie reminds
me of the killer's chilling glare

02:24.110 --> 02:27.705
There is a serial killer at large
going after criminals.

02:28.882 --> 02:32.215
I don 't want to see psychos
even in the movies.

02:35.588 --> 02:38.819
...reminds me of the killer's
chilling glare from the movie.

02:39.893 --> 02:43.624
There is a serial killer at large
going after criminals.

02:44.564 --> 02:48.227
I don 't want to see psychos
even in the movies.

02:49.402 --> 02:51.632
I hope you enjoy
the rest of the night.

02:51.704 --> 02:54.002
and that tomorrow will be
another movie-like day.

02:54.073 --> 02:55.734
This is Ko Sun-young
saying goodbye.

02:58.811 --> 03:04.579
MlDNlGHT F.M.

03:07.854 --> 03:09.287
She's here!

03:09.355 --> 03:10.583
Clap, everyone!

03:28.474 --> 03:29.907
Charismatic announcer turned
radio DJ

03:29.976 --> 03:31.944
How fresh she looked!

03:32.011 --> 03:33.911
Those were her good days.

03:33.980 --> 03:35.311
You're right

03:36.616 --> 03:40.814
What's with sudden interest
in studying abroad?

03:40.887 --> 03:43.219
So that I can take your job
when I come back.

03:44.891 --> 03:47.121
I don't think she's kidding.

03:47.794 --> 03:49.819
As if she ever does!

03:51.497 --> 03:54.933
Studying is just an excuse
I need some time off.

03:55.001 --> 03:56.332
Plus, there is
my daughter's operation.

03:56.402 --> 04:01.362
Being a single mom is
definitely not easy.

04:02.141 --> 04:03.665
She'll be fine.

04:07.647 --> 04:11.879
Declared innocent
by lack of evidence

04:11.951 --> 04:17.685
Leaves us all puzzled as to
where there is any justice

04:17.757 --> 04:20.658
Obviously, Judicature has lost it.

04:20.726 --> 04:21.921
Judicature has lost it!

04:22.962 --> 04:26.557
Still makes my hair stand
to think about that time.

04:26.633 --> 04:28.294
Resigns as a news reporter

04:28.368 --> 04:31.132
Come back after 2 years.

04:31.204 --> 04:34.196
I'll put you back in the newsroom.

04:34.907 --> 04:39.810
What's the point when she'll
get kicked out right away?

04:40.580 --> 04:43.811
Somebody is upset about
Sun-young's departure.

04:44.584 --> 04:46.108
Where is Se-yeon?

04:46.185 --> 04:49.120
The new girl can't be
bothered to show her face?

04:49.188 --> 04:51.520
She's been out of reach
since last night.

04:51.591 --> 04:56.927
Old one or the new one alike,
they have no respect for the producer.

04:58.798 --> 05:00.663
I should get going.

05:03.836 --> 05:04.564
Producer Oh.

05:09.242 --> 05:10.573
What are you doing?

05:11.044 --> 05:18.177
I don't feel so generous as to
wish you good luck.

05:19.385 --> 05:20.682
Can we get over this?

05:21.354 --> 05:23.515
You want to make up?

05:23.589 --> 05:26.251
So, you wrote up your own
little playlist and faxed it over?

05:26.326 --> 05:27.486
What fax?

05:27.560 --> 05:29.619
- What's he talking about?
- Forget it!

05:30.897 --> 05:35.596
Don't get your hopes up about
getting your TV job back.

05:37.270 --> 05:38.100
It's not happening.

05:40.773 --> 05:43.503
Where are you going, sir?
What about the show?

05:56.422 --> 06:01.223
Don't you know how busy I am?

06:01.294 --> 06:03.660
I'm not a family babysitter.

06:03.730 --> 06:09.100
Even Jun-young had me pick up
Hye-ji from the airport.

06:09.168 --> 06:10.863
What a handful!

06:10.937 --> 06:13.269
Eun-soo, what are you doing up?

06:15.241 --> 06:17.471
She's still up?!

06:17.543 --> 06:21.479
Your mom is angry
because you're still up.

06:23.983 --> 06:25.678
Share your bed
with your cousin tonight.

06:25.752 --> 06:28.380
What you doing up, honey?

06:29.155 --> 06:31.089
You could miss the flight tomorrow

06:31.157 --> 06:32.590
So go to bed now.

06:32.658 --> 06:34.091
If you agree, tap tap tap.

06:35.962 --> 06:36.894
Once more.

06:39.265 --> 06:40.789
Good girl

06:40.867 --> 06:43.461
From tomorrow, mommy will
spend more time with you

06:43.536 --> 06:44.503
Put your auntie on.

06:46.472 --> 06:50.602
I have to stay up for work.

06:50.676 --> 06:52.735
What the hell?

06:52.812 --> 06:55.610
Can I send in my request by text?

06:55.681 --> 07:00.675
I'm really not in the mood
So, please stop talking nonsense?

07:00.753 --> 07:03.187
Hey, I'm a listener, too!

07:03.256 --> 07:04.655
We started together,
we end it together

07:04.724 --> 07:06.715
I can be an annoying listener

07:07.727 --> 07:09.058
Don't fool around.

07:10.730 --> 07:13.893
Get Eun-soo into bed for me?
I'll check in later.

07:13.966 --> 07:18.665
All right! Don't be a pathetic
crybaby for the last show

07:19.539 --> 07:21.302
Go get it, sis!

07:21.374 --> 07:22.068
Sun-young!

07:23.643 --> 07:24.974
All right. Gotta go.

07:26.546 --> 07:27.171
Come on.

07:29.816 --> 07:33.115
A single tap for no and
three for yes, is it?

07:33.186 --> 07:35.586
Isn't it better
to just text each other?

07:35.655 --> 07:37.680
I don't want her
to forget how to talk

07:38.458 --> 07:40.983
She's putting up with so much...

07:41.060 --> 07:42.925
So many operations.

07:42.995 --> 07:45.691
Will she get a better result
in the States?

07:45.765 --> 07:47.289
She will
I know she will.

07:47.366 --> 07:49.994
Difficulties following the homicide

07:50.069 --> 07:52.299
at the red light district,
the police...

07:52.371 --> 07:54.362
Red light district!
Difficulties!

07:54.440 --> 07:56.601
concentrate on the crackdown

07:56.676 --> 07:59.201
Red light... Red-light District

07:59.278 --> 08:03.442
Are you serious about
going back into TV?

08:03.516 --> 08:05.848
Makes me look like an ass, right?

08:05.918 --> 08:10.048
You actually know that?
and, you're still doing that?

08:14.427 --> 08:15.655
What the heck?

08:15.728 --> 08:17.161
Jesus Christ!

08:17.230 --> 08:18.162
Are you all right?

08:18.731 --> 08:20.562
Is he out of his mind?

08:25.938 --> 08:28.168
Come back here!

08:29.709 --> 08:32.269
Oh, my god!
What's he doing?

08:32.345 --> 08:35.075
- What the! Let me...
- Stay in the car

08:36.948 --> 08:38.883
He's going to kill her!

08:38.951 --> 08:40.679
Out in plain sight...

08:40.753 --> 08:43.688
It scares me to raise a daughter
with a scum like that around.

08:46.192 --> 08:50.686
It's obvious he's stone drunk.
Shall I call the cops?

08:50.763 --> 08:53.994
Forget it. No good can come
out of getting involved.

08:54.066 --> 08:55.294
What the fuck are
you looking at?

08:55.968 --> 08:58.095
We'll get off here.

08:58.671 --> 08:59.660
What a creep!

09:02.542 --> 09:04.134
Pick up the damn phone...

09:05.211 --> 09:07.338
The person you're calling...

09:07.413 --> 09:11.042
You'll be a pain in the ass, too?

09:12.652 --> 09:15.416
Lost your mind?
Call me right away!

09:22.228 --> 09:25.629
Eun-soo, I made this for you.

09:25.698 --> 09:28.360
Promise me you'll
wear it every night?

09:28.834 --> 09:33.271
Good. Now, go to sleep.

09:36.576 --> 09:39.170
I can't. I've got work to do

09:39.245 --> 09:41.475
Go to sleep! Now!

09:57.063 --> 09:59.657
As 7th victim from the recent
serial murder has emerged,

09:59.732 --> 10:03.293
the police have announced
reinforcement of the task force team

10:03.369 --> 10:05.894
This is Jang Seok-hyun
from GCN News.

10:13.679 --> 10:16.671
Anything you want to add?

10:16.749 --> 10:18.410
Looks like they're having fun.

10:22.321 --> 10:25.256
Guess what? Our show could
go down the same road.

10:25.324 --> 10:29.021
Mr. Oh is eager to rebuild
the program from the inside out.

10:29.595 --> 10:31.529
I think he'll get on well
with the new girl

10:31.597 --> 10:32.825
I don't think so...

10:32.898 --> 10:36.129
With you gone,
the ratings will drop.

10:36.202 --> 10:38.329
And by next fall,
we'll get the axe.

10:44.877 --> 10:48.335
You know Deok-tae?
He's tonight's guest.

10:49.015 --> 10:50.039
But, I thought it was someone else.

10:50.116 --> 10:52.641
The 'Travis' guy didn't
answer my calls

10:52.718 --> 10:54.345
Thank god we found
a replacement in time.

10:56.856 --> 10:59.086
Are you crazy?

10:59.158 --> 11:01.023
That man is a stalker!

11:01.093 --> 11:05.291
I think you're overreacting.

11:05.364 --> 11:08.492
He is an avid listener and
the biggest fan of our show.

11:09.702 --> 11:11.795
We still have time.
Find someone else!

11:12.972 --> 11:13.904
You can't be serious.

11:26.585 --> 11:29.019
Hey, where are you going?

11:29.088 --> 11:31.022
That was very bad.

11:31.090 --> 11:32.819
Come and have a seat

11:32.892 --> 11:36.123
Give me your phone

11:37.096 --> 11:38.723
What have you got here?

11:39.632 --> 11:41.031
2424? What are you, a mover?

11:43.969 --> 11:47.769
Is that why you have
those broad shoulders?

11:49.642 --> 11:53.738
She won't be using this
number from tomorrow.

11:54.647 --> 11:55.409
Saved

12:00.119 --> 12:03.452
What do you see in her?
She a mom, you know?

12:04.290 --> 12:10.320
She has... a divine voice.

12:12.732 --> 12:15.292
Real soft up in your ears.

12:15.367 --> 12:17.801
Like a soft tongue?

12:22.975 --> 12:24.306
You're dirty.

12:25.044 --> 12:28.013
I'll give you a shout later.
Go to the bathroom.

12:28.080 --> 12:30.708
Switch off the cell...
Do it now

12:34.186 --> 12:37.314
He is a just fan.
We can't change him now.

12:38.758 --> 12:39.656
Did you see this?

12:41.293 --> 12:44.820
Look at those muscles!

12:44.897 --> 12:47.661
There is only a fine line between
a fan and a stalker.

12:47.733 --> 12:50.634
Let your guard down and
they'll walk all over you

12:51.704 --> 12:56.232
It's your fans that keep
you on your job.

12:56.308 --> 12:58.333
Make sure you get that
to the new girl as well.

12:58.410 --> 13:00.571
The minute you let them
take control, it's over.

13:00.646 --> 13:01.977
Whatever you say!

13:03.449 --> 13:07.476
Totally oblivious of this.

13:10.589 --> 13:13.888
How about coming in
on time for once?

13:13.959 --> 13:16.052
- What a beautiful night!
- Hi!

13:16.128 --> 13:17.789
It's the last show.
You could have come early

13:18.364 --> 13:19.092
Coffee?

13:19.165 --> 13:21.292
...and donuts! Oops!

13:21.367 --> 13:22.299
Go on.

13:22.368 --> 13:24.097
They're fattening

13:24.170 --> 13:25.762
You said I should
put on some weight

13:25.838 --> 13:27.203
Did you check the CDs?

13:27.273 --> 13:28.900
Am I your maid?

13:30.876 --> 13:33.208
- My sweetheart
- Cut it out!

13:33.279 --> 13:35.509
Thank you for this!

13:35.581 --> 13:37.208
It's nothing

13:37.283 --> 13:38.648
Let me see

13:38.717 --> 13:40.412
I'm impressed!

13:41.987 --> 13:46.515
It is quite hard to take in but

13:46.592 --> 13:49.618
it's our dear friend's last show.

13:51.397 --> 13:52.830
In 5 minutes.

15:13.545 --> 15:16.275
What's gotten into him?

15:31.463 --> 15:32.987
Sam?

15:35.768 --> 15:37.201
Sam!

15:39.872 --> 15:40.804
Sam!

15:42.074 --> 15:43.803
Where are you?

15:56.555 --> 15:58.216
You scared me.

15:59.792 --> 16:04.559
You'll wake Eun-soo up
if you scream like that.

16:12.638 --> 16:17.871
I said stop screaming.

16:18.544 --> 16:21.377
Stop!

16:26.852 --> 16:29.685
What do you want?

16:29.755 --> 16:30.983
Shhh...

18:15.828 --> 18:16.556
Eun-soo!

19:44.416 --> 19:48.079
Have you ever had
coffee with an angel?

19:48.153 --> 19:51.714
This program is brought to you

19:51.790 --> 19:54.190
by angels' choice of coffee,
Angel-in-us

19:55.360 --> 20:01.299
3... 2... 1!

20:13.478 --> 20:18.108
Did you have another
movie-like day?

20:18.183 --> 20:22.119
Hi, this is Ko Sun-young
from Midnight F.M.

20:22.988 --> 20:31.418
Tonight will be the precious
last time that I share with you.

20:31.496 --> 20:40.529
I hope the next two hours will
be an unforgettable experience.

20:41.907 --> 20:42.931
Our last...

20:45.110 --> 20:50.309
I never thought I would
ever say these words.

20:50.382 --> 20:53.180
Tonight we're going to
talk about farewells.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.186
There she goes again!
Why bother writing up the script?

20:55.254 --> 20:59.350
If I were to pick the most
beautiful farewells in the movie.

21:00.959 --> 21:02.688
What's wrong with you today?

21:02.761 --> 21:05.059
I would choose last scene
from Casablanca.

21:05.130 --> 21:07.894
I'm a bit of a romantic.

21:07.966 --> 21:10.298
At the foggy Moroccan airport.

21:10.369 --> 21:14.032
two people stand facing each other
unable to speak their mind.

21:14.106 --> 21:17.803
Ilsa boarding the plane and
Rick watching on.

21:19.177 --> 21:23.807
A farewell scene that was
as beautiful as it was heartbreaking.

21:25.484 --> 21:29.614
What would our farewell be like?

21:33.191 --> 21:35.523
It's a text from a listener.

21:35.594 --> 21:37.027
It says

21:37.095 --> 21:42.226
Love that lasts the longest is
love that never returns.

21:43.468 --> 21:47.029
I suppose that parting
could be...

21:47.105 --> 21:50.040
a way to preserve your love forever.

21:50.108 --> 21:53.942
The queen of improvisation!

21:57.316 --> 21:58.044
What is this?

21:59.418 --> 22:01.682
The reason why so many fans
still remember James Dean.

22:01.753 --> 22:03.277
Somerset Maugham
could be because of

22:03.355 --> 22:07.086
his unexpected early farewell

22:07.693 --> 22:11.094
A listener who sent in
the Somerset Maugham quote.

22:11.163 --> 22:14.599
you forgot to give us your name
but thank you.

22:14.666 --> 22:17.100
You could call this the love
theme song of "Casablanca"

22:17.169 --> 22:19.399
'As time goes by'

22:20.072 --> 22:22.597
They won't notice that
this was an accident?

22:22.674 --> 22:24.801
How could they?
When she's that smooth.

22:25.577 --> 22:27.408
Take it easy, relax!

22:28.680 --> 22:31.410
You nervous? Forgetting to
switch off your cell.

22:33.485 --> 22:35.112
It's officially the final show.

22:35.187 --> 22:37.280
Even Ms. Perfect is making mistakes.

22:37.356 --> 22:39.415
I've never seen her make
a mistake since her first broadcast.

22:39.491 --> 22:40.958
It's your fault.

22:41.026 --> 22:42.618
She's low on caffeine.

22:43.895 --> 22:45.419
I could use a cup of coffee.

22:45.497 --> 22:47.590
You heard her! Get some
donuts and cheesecake, too.

22:47.666 --> 22:49.930
People will remember
this show forever

22:50.001 --> 22:52.333
Shall we go together then?
Consider it a date.

22:52.404 --> 22:55.635
Go on. It's still quite early.
I can manage by myself.

22:56.408 --> 22:58.069
I don't like where this is going...

22:59.511 --> 23:02.776
- You said my pot belly...
- I know you want it, too

23:15.260 --> 23:19.594
Hey, sis! Are you trying
to pull tricks on me?

23:25.670 --> 23:30.004
I know you're trying
to loosen me up.

23:30.075 --> 23:32.202
but tonight's show is
really important for me.

23:33.278 --> 23:37.305
Ko Sun-young?
Did you get my fax?

23:38.483 --> 23:39.313
Who is this?

23:39.384 --> 23:42.012
You'll play the songs
as it appears on the list.

23:42.988 --> 23:46.719
Because I'm holding
your family hostage.

23:46.792 --> 23:47.622
What?

23:47.692 --> 23:52.026
Or your sister will die.

23:54.199 --> 23:55.131
What?

24:06.545 --> 24:08.376
A-young, who was that just now?

24:08.447 --> 24:09.880
Listen carefully.

24:09.948 --> 24:15.284
You try to tell anyone about
this situation and I kill them

24:15.353 --> 24:16.285
Hello?

24:17.556 --> 24:18.488
Hello?

24:34.973 --> 24:36.406
Hello? Police?

24:36.475 --> 24:38.340
I can't reach home.

24:38.410 --> 24:40.503
Could you send someone
to look around?

24:42.781 --> 24:44.908
Detective Cho, check this out.

24:46.418 --> 24:47.715
Something is wrong.

24:49.588 --> 24:53.957
Face covered up and bow-like knot
looks like our serial killer's

24:54.025 --> 24:56.892
But he's only been going after
pimps and drug dealers.

24:56.962 --> 24:58.327
Is she one of them?

24:59.531 --> 25:00.759
Who reported this in?

25:00.832 --> 25:04.165
The killer called in to say
he left her body here.

25:04.236 --> 25:05.168
Detectives!

25:08.540 --> 25:10.167
The suspect called himself?

25:14.346 --> 25:15.870
It's the producer from
the radio show.

25:15.947 --> 25:17.778
- I'm Detective Cho.
- Oh Jung-moo.

25:17.849 --> 25:19.908
I'm sorry to have called
you so late.

25:19.985 --> 25:23.477
but the victim's cell phone had
multiple calls from you

26:22.948 --> 26:24.381
Hang in there.

26:25.550 --> 26:26.983
It won't take long.

26:29.888 --> 26:31.685
Who is that kid?

26:38.263 --> 26:42.597
Where is Sun-young's daughter?

27:01.720 --> 27:04.848
She's... in the hospital.

27:05.724 --> 27:10.058
Because... she hurt... her neck.

27:10.128 --> 27:13.962
Those of you still up at this hour
and listening to this show

27:14.032 --> 27:17.968
send in texts to #2112.

27:19.037 --> 27:21.062
'Sun-young,
is this really the end?'

27:21.139 --> 27:23.767
'You already kept me company
through the night'

27:24.843 --> 27:26.572
Hi, Ms Bridget Jones,

27:26.645 --> 27:30.877
it's you guys who kept me company

27:31.549 --> 27:33.983
Tomorrow morning,
tell me the sky is white...

27:34.052 --> 27:35.849
then, I'll reply that
the clouds are black'

27:35.920 --> 27:36.579
It's black.

27:37.589 --> 27:39.022
'Travis'! You quoted from...

27:39.157 --> 27:41.591
- "Les amants du Pont-Neuf"
- "Les amants du Pont-Neuf"

27:44.062 --> 27:50.797
This quote reminds of the
scene where the heroine leaves

27:51.670 --> 27:53.695
And my heart starts to ache.

27:53.772 --> 27:56.798
I feel that I've broken
a promise I made with you

27:56.875 --> 27:58.866
because of personal reasons.

27:58.943 --> 28:01.275
Mr. Ko Joon-young...

28:01.346 --> 28:03.280
- So, you're her brother.
- That's right.

28:03.348 --> 28:04.838
But in the movie, the lovers
are eventually.

28:04.916 --> 28:05.780
But, it's a protocol.

28:06.818 --> 28:10.151
We still have to take a look around.

28:14.826 --> 28:15.758
Well...

28:18.329 --> 28:19.261
If you must.

28:20.932 --> 28:24.060
Pont Neuf is the oldest bridge
in Paris

28:24.135 --> 28:25.432
But its name actually
means a 'new bridge'

28:25.503 --> 28:31.066
Thank you and sorry to be a bother.

28:32.043 --> 28:34.170
What a nice place.

28:35.747 --> 28:37.681
You have upstairs, too?

28:37.749 --> 28:39.979
The radio is a little too loud

28:40.051 --> 28:42.986
I'm already jealous that
she'll get more love.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.630
I missed 3 minutes of the show.

29:03.208 --> 29:07.042
I hope you'll give her just as much

29:09.514 --> 29:11.038
love and attention.

29:17.322 --> 29:18.346
I'm going back up.

29:18.423 --> 29:23.952
The next song is from
Michael Haneke's "Pianist"

29:24.028 --> 29:27.464
another film about obsessive love.

29:44.349 --> 29:45.373
Hey, Sun-young.

29:46.251 --> 29:48.879
I told you not to tell anyone.

29:48.953 --> 29:50.921
Why did you call the police?

29:50.989 --> 29:53.787
Why won't you listen to me?!

29:57.562 --> 30:01.692
Now I'll show you what
the consequences are.

30:22.287 --> 30:24.414
Listen very carefully.

30:25.490 --> 30:29.620
You cannot tell anyone
about this situation

30:29.694 --> 30:32.219
Who are you?
Are you a friend of A-young's?

30:32.297 --> 30:33.321
Stop this sick joke!

30:34.499 --> 30:40.131
Does this look like a joke to you?

30:41.306 --> 30:43.740
Does it?

30:48.012 --> 30:49.445
Look!

30:49.514 --> 30:54.850
I am holding your family hostage.

30:55.620 --> 30:59.647
Where is your daughter anyway?

30:59.724 --> 31:02.090
I only see this kid.

31:06.364 --> 31:09.697
She's in the hospital.
She hurt her neck.

31:09.767 --> 31:12.201
Please...
Why are you doing this?

31:20.678 --> 31:24.512
Hey! I'm telling the truth!

31:28.119 --> 31:29.518
From this moment,

31:29.587 --> 31:32.613
you'll be running the show
according to my instructions

31:32.690 --> 31:34.920
You got my fax, right?

31:35.593 --> 31:38.426
So, you faxed over
your own little playlist?

31:43.001 --> 31:45.834
I put a lot of thoughts into that,
you know

31:45.904 --> 31:47.735
I don't have it with me.
Somebody took it away.

31:52.210 --> 31:55.236
I hope you won't
disappoint me anymore.

31:58.716 --> 32:02.880
Shouldn't we try for
a beautiful ending?

32:04.355 --> 32:07.381
I'll tell you what you
should play next.

32:18.703 --> 32:21.103
July 18, 2005...

32:26.577 --> 32:29.808
Was the first week after you
started the show.

32:30.581 --> 32:32.515
I want the first song
you played that day.

32:34.385 --> 32:37.821
Trouble recalling?
Let me give you a clue.

32:37.889 --> 32:40.221
It's a bit like our relationship.

32:41.492 --> 32:45.519
The main character was a DJ.

32:46.698 --> 32:47.824
Quite a bit actually.

32:48.599 --> 32:51.363
"Play Misty for Me",
"Good Morning Vietnam"

32:51.436 --> 32:53.927
"Fisher King", "Talk to Me"

32:54.405 --> 32:55.337
The list goes on.

33:01.446 --> 33:05.883
You're going to find that song
and play it.

33:05.950 --> 33:09.579
right after this one.

33:15.159 --> 33:16.786
38551

33:16.861 --> 33:18.988
What are you doing here?

33:21.265 --> 33:23.597
Woo-han, when this song
ends play the ads.

33:23.668 --> 33:24.794
What?

33:24.869 --> 33:27.201
Don't play any songs!
Just the ads!

33:30.008 --> 33:30.975
Ko A-young

33:33.378 --> 33:34.402
Look at this

33:38.883 --> 33:40.817
Now, it's all up to your sister.

34:00.338 --> 34:01.669
Are you... okay?

34:36.274 --> 34:36.899
Sun-young!

34:37.574 --> 34:38.599
What’s the matter with you?

34:40.277 --> 34:42.405
Hey, stop it!

34:48.585 --> 34:51.418
What's the matter?

34:52.290 --> 34:54.417
What's this about?

34:54.492 --> 34:55.719
From when?

34:55.793 --> 34:57.317
July 18, 2005!

34:58.196 --> 34:59.629
I must find the first song
I played that day

34:59.697 --> 35:02.165
What the...

35:03.267 --> 35:10.366
It was 'Everybody knows'
from "Pump up the volume"

35:10.441 --> 35:13.672
You know that? From memory?!

35:14.545 --> 35:15.477
It's right...

35:18.649 --> 35:19.911
'Everybody knows'/ "Pump up the volume"

35:19.984 --> 35:21.576
Holy shit! He's right.

35:23.154 --> 35:24.178
This is all you need?

35:27.492 --> 35:30.290
You really are a stalker!

35:31.162 --> 35:32.186
That's creepy.

35:33.598 --> 35:37.796
Find "Pump up the volume"
OST from the database.

35:37.869 --> 35:40.804
Pump up the volume!
P! U! M! P!

35:40.872 --> 35:43.102
It's not on the database.
Try the shelf.

35:43.174 --> 35:46.803
What kind of database is that?
Pathetic!

35:47.778 --> 35:48.802
Found it! Hang on...

35:49.981 --> 35:52.814
Shit! The case is empty

35:53.551 --> 35:55.883
Can you download an MP3
or something?

35:55.953 --> 35:57.818
Are you for real?
We are a radio station

35:57.889 --> 35:59.857
Is it the sound quality?
Listeners won't notice.

35:59.924 --> 36:02.950
Why on earth do we need it anyway?

36:03.027 --> 36:05.154
I don't know, either.

36:05.229 --> 36:08.960
Look up Leonard Cohen discography.

36:09.033 --> 36:11.467
You're right!
It's a Leonard Cohen song.

36:11.536 --> 36:12.366
I'll be right over.

36:13.037 --> 36:15.665
- Excuse me, Mr. Oh.
- Yes.

36:15.740 --> 36:18.971
We haven't notified the family, yet.

36:21.512 --> 36:23.480
Please keep it discreet.

36:24.916 --> 36:26.076
It's track 3

36:26.150 --> 36:28.175
I had to play six public
service ads in a row.

36:28.252 --> 36:29.184
What the matter with her?

36:29.253 --> 36:30.982
She has completely lost it.

36:31.055 --> 36:33.080
What a sure way to screw up.

36:33.157 --> 36:35.990
I'll have to write
a thousand report on this.

36:41.265 --> 36:43.199
Talk about something after this ad
while I get the song ready.

36:43.267 --> 36:45.292
while I get the song ready.

36:57.114 --> 37:03.246
Maybe because it's my last show.

37:05.323 --> 37:08.451
I 'm getting really nervous.

37:10.328 --> 37:11.955
I hope you'll understand

37:14.732 --> 37:16.757
Even if I seem to be
acting a little strange.

37:18.236 --> 37:19.760
Wake up! Wake up!

37:20.738 --> 37:25.573
It's just... really hard
for me today

37:25.643 --> 37:27.167
because I don't want it
to be the end.

37:29.847 --> 37:33.476
Originally, I wanted to
talk about farewell

37:33.551 --> 37:36.281
as the subject of the last show.

37:37.054 --> 37:41.286
But, let me just play the songs
you want like always.

37:44.662 --> 37:47.028
Wake up! Wake up!

37:50.868 --> 37:54.804
My apologies. I must
have been too sentimental.

37:55.273 --> 37:59.505
Up next is 'Everybody knows'
from "Pump up the volume"

37:59.910 --> 38:02.242
Where the hero was a DJ.

38:02.313 --> 38:08.149
A shy teenager, Mark
becomes a DJ at night

38:08.219 --> 38:10.551
and enthralls fellow teenagers.

38:10.621 --> 38:17.754
Through broadcasting
he discovers himself changing.

38:18.429 --> 38:19.760
Here is the song.

38:37.882 --> 38:41.682
We need to talk
What is it?

38:42.520 --> 38:43.680
Is it Mr. Oh?

38:45.456 --> 38:47.390
He won't get off your case?

38:48.859 --> 38:49.985
Excuse me

38:51.962 --> 38:52.986
Well, l...

39:12.717 --> 39:16.244
It aint...

39:16.320 --> 39:17.753
What do you mean?

39:17.822 --> 39:19.346
I dug up the old cue sheet...

39:21.726 --> 39:27.255
I specifically requested the song
you played on July 18, 2005.

39:27.331 --> 39:31.461
And the version you played
wasn't Leonard Cohen's.

39:33.337 --> 39:35.271
It was the Concrete Blonde.

39:35.339 --> 39:37.364
You even said yourself.

39:37.441 --> 39:39.875
that Cohen version
was in the movie

39:39.944 --> 39:42.071
but not on the OST!

39:42.980 --> 39:44.971
You don't even remember
what you said.

39:45.883 --> 39:47.475
I am really disappointed.

40:02.867 --> 40:04.698
Who are you talking to?

40:05.870 --> 40:06.802
Sun-young!

40:10.474 --> 40:12.203
Sun-young!

40:13.077 --> 40:16.103
Open the door!

40:18.783 --> 40:21.013
Look! Ko Sun-young!

40:26.690 --> 40:29.454
If you hang up on me again,

40:29.527 --> 40:31.324
I'll fucking kill them all!

40:32.296 --> 40:34.127
I'll give you one more
chance to make up...

40:34.698 --> 40:36.723
With the next song.

40:41.305 --> 40:43.330
Oh, my god! A-young...

40:44.809 --> 40:46.333
Please... what is it that you want?

40:46.410 --> 40:49.038
Is it money?
I'll give you it to you.

40:52.716 --> 40:54.843
It's not money that I want.

40:54.919 --> 40:57.251
Let's meet up
I'll come over to you.

40:58.923 --> 40:59.890
You'll come here?

41:00.458 --> 41:02.483
How can you be so irresponsible?

41:02.560 --> 41:04.687
This is your last broadcast!

41:04.762 --> 41:09.199
Wasn't it your idea to make
a memorable time with your fans?

41:09.266 --> 41:12.702
And, now... you'll abandon
the show and come here?

41:13.270 --> 41:14.999
Hey... please!
What is this about?

41:15.072 --> 41:18.098
You will not stop the broadcast!
Because, If you do...

41:20.778 --> 41:25.408
It'll be your sister's ankle
not just a toe.

41:25.983 --> 41:32.513
Next is the theme song
from "Taxi Driver"

41:33.891 --> 41:40.729
You must say the exact thing
you said when you.

41:40.898 --> 41:43.423
played that song on Dec 5, 2006.

41:44.301 --> 41:47.327
Come on, Sun-young
You can do this!

41:50.908 --> 41:52.933
You poor little thing.

42:13.264 --> 42:18.201
Do you remember what I said

42:18.269 --> 42:19.793
when we played 'Taxi Driver'?

42:19.870 --> 42:22.896
You're driving me nuts!

42:22.973 --> 42:26.067
Tell me what's going on
so I can help

42:26.143 --> 42:31.513
I'll explain everything later
But now...

42:31.582 --> 42:33.516
You've got to help me out
Please, okay?

42:35.586 --> 42:40.523
Give us at least
some kind of explanation.

43:13.257 --> 43:14.485
Well, the main character Travis
is a taxi driver...

43:14.558 --> 43:17.322
so every night...

43:17.394 --> 43:18.383
No... no!

43:50.527 --> 43:53.291
You said you remember
all my shows.

43:53.597 --> 43:54.325
That's right...

43:55.899 --> 43:57.833
December 5, 2006.

43:58.702 --> 44:00.761
What did I say when l
played the song from "Taxi driver"?

44:03.941 --> 44:06.466
This song is finishing
Shall I play another advert?

44:06.543 --> 44:08.875
Quickly! Think!

44:13.851 --> 44:19.187
Travis, a hero grows...

44:19.256 --> 44:20.780
through suffering

44:21.058 --> 44:24.391
A hero grows through suffering.

44:24.461 --> 44:25.985
I have never heard before

44:26.063 --> 44:30.693
They could no longer put up
with the corrupt world...

44:31.769 --> 44:33.600
So, they had to stand up.

44:34.872 --> 44:35.896
Taxi driver

44:40.778 --> 44:42.507
"HBC Radio"

44:43.480 --> 44:46.711
That was 'Everybody knows'
from "Pump up the volume"

44:47.484 --> 44:49.418
You have to tell me
what the situation is

44:51.689 --> 44:54.624
Stop making prank calls to 911.

44:54.692 --> 44:57.718
By killing the pimps and
rescuing the prostitute, lris,

44:58.195 --> 45:00.459
Travis earns the title of hero.

45:01.432 --> 45:03.263
Was he really a hero?

45:04.334 --> 45:09.271
At time, I said a hero grows
through suffering'

45:10.941 --> 45:14.877
In the movie, Travis is
portrayed as a maladjusted man.

45:16.046 --> 45:17.377
But if you think about it,

45:17.448 --> 45:19.882
all heroes are like that
to a certain extent.

45:19.950 --> 45:23.386
Because they cannot endure
the corruption of society,

45:23.454 --> 45:27.083
so they must act.

45:27.157 --> 45:28.488
Right answer! Clap Clap

45:31.361 --> 45:33.989
Are you out of your mind?

45:34.698 --> 45:36.393
What do you think you're doing!

45:38.368 --> 45:40.700
I said unless the world changes,
we can only wait for heroes to rise

45:40.771 --> 45:44.502
Are you all trying
to finish the show?

45:44.575 --> 45:47.100
Don't shout at me
I'm fed up too

45:47.177 --> 45:49.509
I suddenly remember this

45:50.180 --> 45:53.411
Let's fuck it up and
hand in our resignations!

45:53.484 --> 45:58.615
Someday a real rain will come and
wash all the scum off the streets.

45:58.689 --> 46:00.156
She's already introduced
the next song.

46:00.224 --> 46:04.456
If you have any bitter feelings
you wish to get rid of.

46:05.829 --> 46:10.562
Hope you can wash them away
with this song...

46:21.678 --> 46:24.579
You want to fuck up?
Let's finish it off.

46:24.648 --> 46:29.085
- The music! Change the song!
- Screw you! All of you!

46:46.270 --> 46:50.104
Sun-young... Don't cry.

46:52.676 --> 46:57.409
Do you know where
I've just been?

47:15.032 --> 47:16.556
You were doing so well.

47:18.435 --> 47:20.767
Why are you screwing up now?

47:20.838 --> 47:22.169
It wasn't me.

47:32.549 --> 47:34.574
Your sister is dead because of you.

48:01.812 --> 48:05.646
Shouldn't we work together
for a beautiful ending?

48:08.118 --> 48:10.052
No, then he'll kill her daughter

48:10.120 --> 48:12.850
But we gotta call the cops.

48:12.923 --> 48:15.858
That psycho killed a cop
He's capable of anything.

48:15.926 --> 48:19.555
Exactly! We don't know
if he'll keep his word.

48:24.034 --> 48:27.765
Are you okay?
Who the hell is he?

48:27.838 --> 48:31.171
We saw your phone
He threatened us, too.

48:32.042 --> 48:33.873
Sun-young, check this out.

48:36.446 --> 48:38.880
My sister got killed because of you!

48:38.949 --> 48:42.282
If I only played the right song...
You killed her!

48:42.753 --> 48:45.278
Calm down and check this out.

48:45.756 --> 48:46.688
I don't want to listen to you.

48:52.095 --> 48:53.392
Se-yeon is dead, too.

48:57.467 --> 49:00.334
I just went to identify her body.

49:11.214 --> 49:12.044
What's up?

49:12.115 --> 49:13.446
Hey...

49:14.918 --> 49:16.442
This came in for you.

49:21.625 --> 49:22.853
No name?

49:32.536 --> 49:33.468
What is this?

49:35.572 --> 49:38.973
The police thinks it's connected
to the serial killer.

49:39.042 --> 49:41.670
Maybe he has something
to do with us.

49:43.847 --> 49:46.077
Can you think of anything?

50:19.282 --> 50:20.214
Baby... is that you?

50:23.720 --> 50:26.314
Baby, are you okay?

50:29.092 --> 50:29.820
Eun-soo!

50:31.695 --> 50:35.131
The playroom, you know.

50:35.198 --> 50:37.325
get inside the closet
and stay quiet.

50:38.602 --> 50:40.433
Inside the closet
and stay there, okay?

50:42.639 --> 50:46.131
Mommy will come for you
Hang in there, okay?

51:00.257 --> 51:01.485
What are you doing?

51:01.558 --> 51:02.183
I gotta go.

51:02.259 --> 51:05.194
You should calm down.

51:06.463 --> 51:08.090
Pull yourself together!

51:09.066 --> 51:11.296
Can you get a broadcast van ready?

51:32.389 --> 51:35.222
Leave one phone line open
Put others on hold.

51:35.692 --> 51:37.125
Stay focused!

51:37.194 --> 51:39.128
- You've got the ads?
- Yes, sir!

51:39.196 --> 51:40.823
- Can you give us a hand?
- Relay channel... 3!

51:41.998 --> 51:43.522
Let me take it.

51:43.600 --> 51:48.230
Once you get home,
what will you do?

51:48.939 --> 51:52.431
She's hiding from him in that house.
I can't just wait around.

51:53.810 --> 51:56.040
This is like asking him
to kill you, too.

51:56.513 --> 51:59.346
I can't just sit here
and do nothing.

52:00.550 --> 52:02.677
Have the van meet me
at the front.

52:02.752 --> 52:03.377
Hey! Sun-young!

52:11.761 --> 52:12.989
This is too dangerous.

52:44.794 --> 52:45.818
Are you up now?

52:46.263 --> 52:49.630
You've only done
40 minutes of the show.

52:52.602 --> 52:55.036
Doesn't look like you're
in the studio.

52:55.105 --> 52:57.039
- Where are you?
- The restroom

52:57.107 --> 52:58.039
The restroom?

53:02.045 --> 53:03.171
Why are you doing this to me?

53:03.947 --> 53:05.676
What did I ever do to you?

53:05.749 --> 53:10.482
How uncommitted you must've
been all this time?

53:16.359 --> 53:17.986
Just get to the point.

53:18.061 --> 53:19.187
What is it that you want?

53:19.262 --> 53:23.289
I gave you many chances.

53:23.366 --> 53:25.891
What the fuck do you want,
you psychopath!

53:31.174 --> 53:32.300
Shut up!

53:33.176 --> 53:35.508
Of all people, you cannot
insult me like that.

53:36.680 --> 53:42.710
We've still got so much work
to do together.

53:42.786 --> 53:45.914
and you're bailing out?

53:49.092 --> 53:54.724
That's all fine but you gotta
put things right before you go.

53:54.798 --> 53:56.425
Put what right?

53:59.703 --> 54:02.467
Don't worry.
We still have time.

54:02.539 --> 54:06.168
Part 3, when you take calls

54:06.243 --> 54:09.770
that caller will be me.

54:09.846 --> 54:13.179
I hate it when I get
beat off for that.

54:14.751 --> 54:16.981
Whatever you want.

54:17.053 --> 54:18.384
But, don't touch the kids

54:22.459 --> 54:23.391
Kid... s?

54:50.987 --> 54:54.718
Maybe the kids are tired
of playing hide-and-seek.

54:56.126 --> 54:58.526
Maybe she wants to play ball.

54:59.095 --> 55:00.562
Lay a finger on my daughter,

55:00.630 --> 55:02.461
and, I'll kill you myself!

55:04.034 --> 55:05.865
You're a big fat liar.

55:14.544 --> 55:18.776
Eun-soo! Come out, come out
wherever you are!

55:20.150 --> 55:21.276
Hide!

55:22.752 --> 55:24.982
Don't let him find you!

55:41.805 --> 55:44.205
You can get the call sign
through this.

56:26.149 --> 56:29.175
Do you know where
we're going anyway?

56:30.453 --> 56:31.977
Turn left here.

57:08.825 --> 57:10.452
Damn traffic!

57:12.228 --> 57:13.957
Let's get started.

57:14.030 --> 57:15.054
It's not the time yet...

57:16.032 --> 57:16.862
Signal!

57:19.936 --> 57:22.871
You're listening to Midnight Soundtrack

57:25.542 --> 57:27.567
We're back with part 3 of the show.

57:27.644 --> 57:29.771
In part 3, we'll be connecting
to one of the listeners

57:29.846 --> 57:32.371
and have a live chat.

57:40.056 --> 57:42.684
We already have a caller
I'll put him through.

57:42.759 --> 57:43.783
Hello?

57:43.860 --> 57:45.794
Hi

57:46.763 --> 57:48.594
Can you tell us who you are?

57:49.265 --> 57:50.197
About me?

57:51.668 --> 57:59.507
I'm someone who believes
this program is all about you.

57:59.576 --> 58:02.943
Your partner, Han Dong-soo.

58:03.012 --> 58:05.037
What do you mean by that?

58:05.114 --> 58:06.741
I'm saying that.

58:06.816 --> 58:12.550
I don't think anyone else
can replace you on this program.

58:12.622 --> 58:16.149
An unqualified DJ like Lim Se-yeon?

58:17.126 --> 58:18.957
Simply unacceptable!

58:19.028 --> 58:22.156
Although she won't be able to now,
even if she wants.

58:23.233 --> 58:24.165
Son of a bitch!

58:24.234 --> 58:25.064
What do you for a living?

58:25.134 --> 58:26.465
Look! Hurry!

58:26.536 --> 58:27.560
Can you tell us more...

58:28.638 --> 58:31.072
Hurry!

58:31.441 --> 58:32.874
Hello? Hello?

58:36.145 --> 58:36.975
Hang on a second.

58:37.247 --> 58:39.681
Hurry!

58:41.451 --> 58:42.679
He hung up.

58:44.153 --> 58:47.680
We have a bad connection.
Let's listen to a song first.

58:52.161 --> 58:53.492
Eun-soo!

58:59.903 --> 59:02.838
Hurry, Eun-soo!

59:21.124 --> 59:24.059
Try not to breathe heavily.
And, be careful!

59:24.127 --> 59:25.958
Sun-young, wait a little bit.

59:26.029 --> 59:28.361
There is no time
I think he found my daughter.

59:28.431 --> 59:30.456
Wait till the cops arrive.

59:32.035 --> 59:33.263
Did you call the police?

59:42.879 --> 59:44.369
- Is this it?
- Yes, sir.

59:47.050 --> 59:49.780
Are you crazy?
He killed a cop already.

59:49.852 --> 59:52.082
You're only provoking him!

59:52.155 --> 59:54.487
He's a nutcase!
It's too dangerous.

59:54.557 --> 59:56.388
You can't reason with him.

59:57.393 --> 01:00:00.885
If anything happens to the kids,
I swear I'll kill you.

01:00:00.964 --> 01:00:04.798
Don't do this.
Don't go in there!

01:00:06.369 --> 01:00:09.998
Ex... excuse me...
I'll come with you.

